                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>The United Nations Security Council met on Friday, August 25, from 3 to 6:25 p.
                    m.; for the record, see U.N. document S/PV.490. In the course of the meeting,
                    Mr. Malik referred to and later had read into the record the text of a
                    communication from Chou En-lai, dated August 24, accusing the United States of
                    aggression against the People’s Republic of China by its virtual occupation of
                    Formosa (U.N. document S/1715). Ambassador Gross read the text of a letter from
                    Mr. Austin (S/1716) responding to this charge. For documentation on this
                    subject, see <ref target="frus1950v06#pg_256">volume VI, pages 256</ref> ff.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
